{"key":"processedPost-15822931","value":{"id":15822931,"first":15822610,"last":15823063,"when":1329501771,"utime":"02/17/12 08:02 PM","content":"If there's water left, you have plenty of water, so don't add any.<br /><br />Always leave the weight off for the first ten minutes after steam begins to escape.&nbsp; <b>If you fail to do this, you're building air pressure rather than steam pressure, and it's useless.</b><br /><br />Once you have vented steam for ten minutes, place the weight on and allow pressure to build to 15 psi.&nbsp; At that point, reduce your stove to the minimum setting which will maintain that pressure without excess wiggling of the weight.&nbsp; You'll have to adjust the stove control several times during the process as required.<br />RR","title":"Re: Pressure cooking problem","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}